

          <div id="about">

          <p>The Evaluation library was originally developed as part of the accessibility working group of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenAjax_Alliance">OpenAjax Alliance</a>, when the OpenAjax Alliance ceased operations the accessibility evaluation library was rebranded to the <a href="https://github.com/opena11y/">OpenA11y GitHub organization</a>.

          <p><a href="https://github.com/opena11y/evaluation-library/blob/main/release-notes.md">View the release notes for the evaluation library.</a></p>

          <h2>Mission</h2>

          <ul>
            <li>To support the understanding and use of the following W3C specializations:
              <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.2/">Accessible Rich Internet Application (ARIA) 1.2 Specification</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html-aria/">Accessible Name and Description Computation 1.1</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/accname/">ARIA in HTML Specification</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20/">Web content Accessibility Guidelines 2.0</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/">Web content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/">Web content Accessibility Guidelines 2.2</a></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Open Source for anyone to freely use in their own projects.</li>
            <li>Support the best practices for implementing accessible online resources.</li>
          </ul>

